HARUNA USMAN BIRNIN KEBBI – The Kebbi State Police Command has said that it has arrested two men for raping a minor of 12 years of age, Hassana Abubakar. The police image maker, SP Nafiu Abubakar, stated that one Nura Bello, 30, and his accomplice, one Abdullahi Garba, 25, had at same address lured the victim Hassana into a tent in their pepper farm and forcefully had canal knowledge of her. SP Nafiu added that upon receipt of the information, the command dispatched men who apprehended them immediately and put them in custody. “Their offences are criminal conspiracy, causing harm and rape of a minor which contravenes the laws of the land,” he noted. He added that, the suspects would soon be arraigned for prosecution after proper investigations had been concluded on the matter. He appealed to members of the public to continue to give relevant information to the police, adding that the force remained steadfast and unwavering in their quest to rid the state of criminal elements.